\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 Calliope makes available different types of bar lines and ways of using them.  Examples are shown below. \par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\keepn\fi0\sb240\sa80\li0\ri0\f1\fs32\b1\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0\b To make a bar line\b0  \par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 Select the Bar Line tool  (shown above).  Click on a staff to place the barline where the pointer is.  A system may be populated with bar lines in one command with the \fs24\f1\b0\i0 S\f1 ystem\f2\f2 ®\f1\f1 L\f1 ay Bars\f0  command.  A bar line may be placed after the current selection (if any) by typing Control-M.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\keepn\fi0\sb240\sa80\li0\ri0\f1\fs32\b1\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0\b To alter the barline placement\b0  \par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 As for any staff object, bar lines are automatically placed when the system is adjusted (see \b Adjustment\b0 ).  To otherwise move a bar line, select the bar line and hold the mouse button down to drag the bar line to a desired location.  The  bar line attaches itself to the nearest staff.  While a bar line is  being dragged between staves, its shape changes to a small single-bar line.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 Bar lines automatically adjust their size and style to conform to the staves and systems to which they are attached.  For example, the all-dots barline puts a dot in each space of the staff, no matter how many lines the staff has.  The repeat barlines put two or three dots depending on whether the staff has an odd or even number of lines.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\keepn\fi0\sb240\sa80\li0\ri0\f1\fs32\b1\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0\b The Barline  Inspector\b0   \par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 With the Barline Inspector it is possible to alter the type and properties of a barline.\par
