\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0\fs24\f1\b0\i0 S\f1 how Through Staff\f0\f0 :\f0   This is normally on, but may be switched off for certain types of notations (example below).\f0 \par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0\fs24\f1\b0\i0 S\f1 how Below Staff:\f0\f0  \f0  This is normally off, but if switched on, the bar extends to the top of the staff below (if one exists).  This is used for barring bracketed instrumental systems or for editorial annotations.\f0 \par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0\fs24\f1\b0\i0 S\f1 how Editorial Mark\f0\f0 :\f0   If switched on, a short vertical bar extends above the staff.\f0 \par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0\fs24\f1\b0\i0 D\f1 ashed Lines\f0 :  For bar lines consisting of thin lines, dashed lines are drawn.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0\fs24\f1\b0\i0 D\f1 o not count this bar:\f0   If switched on, this bar is ignored by Calliope's automatic bar counting mechanism.  This is useful in certain cases where invisible bar lines are used, and when notating anacrusis (also called `pick up') bars.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0\fs24\f1\b0\i0 O\f1 verride 5's Bar Number\f0 :  Bar numbering is specified in the Document Preferences Panel. One of the standard bar numbering styles is called "5's", in which every 5th bar is numbered. When the "5's" option is switched on (using the Document Preferences Panel), it is possible to override the automatic placement of bar numbers to individual bars.  \fs24\f1\b0\i0 N\f1 ormal\f0  is the default, and no override will take place.  \fs24\f1\b0\i0 S\f1 uppress Number\f0  ensures that no bar number will appear over the selected barline. \fs24\f1\b0\i0 F\f1 orce Number\f0  will ensure that a number will appear, even if it is not a multiple of 5.  These options take effect only when "5's" format has been chosen in the Document Preferences Panel.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\keepn\fi0\sb240\sa80\li0\ri0\f1\fs32\b1\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 Examples\par
