\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\ql\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 It is conventional to bar bracketed groups of staves with bars showing between staves.  However, this is not a uniformly observed or enforced convention. In particular, in choral music it is customary not to bar between staves, as this would interfere with the legibility of the underlay.  By making barring between staves optional, on a per-bar basis, Calliope provides for any situation that might arise. \par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\ql\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 Finally, to notate a bar at the end of a staff which continues onto the next staff, put an invisible bar at the end of the first staff, and set the "do not count" switch.  This way the bar numbering will remain consistent.\par
